                .image.round.fit
                  a.link(href='#classes')
                    img(src='images/robot.jpg', alt='')
              .col.col2
                h3 Let's learn about functions!
                  h4
                    | Before we get into a function, lets ask what exactly a function is?
                    p
                      | Functions are little snippets of code that do a task for a programmer.
                      | The cool thing about functions are that they can save time. Imagine we had a bunch of robots that needed to do a task like pick up boxes.
                      | Now lets say all robots have a color and can only pick up boxes that are the same color as themselves. If we were to implement this without functions,
                      | we'd have to write very similar code for every different colored robot. If we had a function, however, we can have code that notices what color
                      | an input robot is and can handle what color boxes it needs to pick up.
